  "title": "Student Care Teacher",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a global leader in early years education and one of the major operators in Singapore. There\nis ample career progression within the organisation. </p><p>We are looking for suitable Student Care Teacher to join the team in our branch.</p><p><strong>Would this be the next career for you? </strong></p><ul><li>Monitor primary school children (primary 1 to 6) to ensure completion of daily homework</li><li>Coach students on some of the subjects (ideally, Maths and Language)</li><li>Execute inhouse curriculum virtue lessons </li><li>Support and lead in-house enrichment programs such as sports and dance activities </li><li>Assist in the planning and running of holiday camps</li><li>Provide mentorship, emotional support and conflict resolution for students </li><li>Ensure safety and timely transit of children from school to student centre </li><li>Ensuring in maintaining the centre tidy and clean </li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as required</li></ul><p><strong>If you are someone with the following, let’s chat!</strong></p><ul><li>Prior working experience in working in student care is an advantage.</li><li>Passionate about working with children and a dedication to the moral and academic formation.</li><li>Demonstrates exceptional work ethics and maintains high integrity.</li><li>Demonstrates a team player fostering unity. </li><li>A positive and energetic attitude that can inspire and motivate students.</li></ul><p><strong>Next Steps</strong></p><p>Apply today or contact us to discuss this exciting opportunity.<br />Do note that we will only be in touch if your application is shortlisted.</p><p>Re Source Partners Pte Ltd | 202021170E | 20C0279 </p><p>Kavitha Selvadurai R22110039</p>",
